      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HELL TO THE LINE (3) is on a quick backup and well placed to take this out. Brings a string on narrow defeat and jumped a $2.1F at Warwick the latest, off an impressive 1L defeat at Ipswich. Steps up in distance today, and that should suit him well. FOUR DOZEN OYSTERS (1) peaks off two placings at the track with the near miss two back over this trip, the best of them. He can make the finish again. STRIKE ME PINK (8) didn't get into it at Ipswich but just missed here three back and did a good job at Doomben following. Those efforts would give him hope. ONLYYOUCANREAD (4) has been in and out in his brief career, but has Doomben and Ipswich form that suggests better things to come. Has the inside gate and can get some of the better prize money. PROUD MISS (7) was poor last time, but his efforts prior would have him in the mix.",
